India’s 10-Year Bonds Decline for First Time in Three Days

-- B y   V   R a m a k r i s h n a n
-- 
2011-09-26T03:37:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/india-s-10-year-bonds-decline-for-first-time-in-three-days.html
India ’s 10-year bonds dropped for
the first time in three days. The yield on the 7.80 percent bond
due April 2021 rose one basis point to 8.31 percent as of 9:07
a.m. in Mumbai, according to the central bank’s trading system.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
